LEMON BARS

CRUST

* 2 Cups Flour
* 1/2 Cup Sugar
* Pinch of salt
* 3/4 Cup Cold Butter
* 1 tsp cold water
* 1/2 cup chopped nuts- I use almonds

1. Sift flour, sugar and salt together add nuts.  
2. Incorporate butter with pastry blender or just work it in with your hands until the dough is crumbly. 
3. Press into the bottom of a 9x12 pan. (I spray the pan with baking spray and line the bottom with parchment). 
4. Bake at 350 for 15-20 minutes until the edges are barely golden. 

LEMON LAYER

* 4 Eggs
* 2 Cups Sugar
* 2 Tbls Flour
* 1/2 Tsp baking powder
* Grated rind of two lemons 
* 1/4 cup (or more) lemon juice

1. Beat everything together and pour over hot crust.  
2. Bake at 350 for 25 minutes. 
3. Edges will be golden.
